p:
The dataset presented here is a long-term, comprehensive record of physical, chemical, and biological measurements of a diverse set of lakes undergoing the effects of a changing climate while recovering from acidification. It is a harmonization of multiple open and unpublished data sources, including the Adirondack Effects Assessment Program (AEAP) Aquatic Biota Survey (
 www.rpi.edu/dept/DFWI/research/aeap/aeap_research.html), the Adirondack Long Term Monitoring Program (ALTM; 
 www.adirondacklakessurvey.org), and the North American Land Data Assimilation System (NLDAS; 
 http://ldas.gsfc.nasa.gov/nldas), and represents a more diverse, long-term data record of Adirondack lakes than has been previously available.
